title: World-famous Danish restaurant Noma will spend the summer in Sydney
text:
Topix › Pacific Travel › World-famous Danish restaurant Noma w... World-famous Danish restaurant Noma will spend the summer in Sydney Next Story Prev Story 34 min ago Read more: The Age 
Copenhagen, Denmark-based Noma, which is consistently ranked among the world's top restaurants, will relocate to Sydney's Barangaroo waterfront for 10 weeks from January with a menu focused on showcasing Australia's shoreline produce and culture. Judging by the popularity of UK-restaurant The Fat Duck's six month stay at Crown Melbourne, where bookings were sold out rapidly despite the $525 price-tag, there is likely to be high demand for bookings from locals.
